title: OSRS #1 - Lake Hope
description: The first stop in the Ohio Spring Race Series at Lake Hope State Park. This Lake Hope race offers a challenging 20 mile rolling course with two big climbs. Many of you who have raced collegiately will remember this OU/OSU race course.
registration: REGISTRATION:  Online registration is available at BikeReg.com.  Online registration will close at 6PM on Friday, March 15, 2013.  Pre-registration is highly encouraged.  A $10 late fee will be assessed to all day of event registrations except juniors.  Onsite registration and check in will be at the Shelter house past the beach area at Lake Hope State Park 27331 State Route 278, McArthur, Ohio 45651 and will be open 8 AM until 9:30 AM on race day for the first wave and 10 AM to 12 PM for the second wave.
notes:
RULES AND REGULATIONS:  All USA Cycling rules and regulations must be followed and will be enforced.  All riders must have a current USA Cycling racing license or a one-day license.  One-day licenses will be available at check in and can only be used by Cat 5 Men, Cat 4 Women and Juniors.  The promoter reserves the right to combine categories based upon number of riders.  The $3 charge for USA Cycling Insurance is covered by the above entry fees. NO REFUNDS DUE TO INCLEMENT WEATHER, INJURY, SICKNESS, OR ACTS OF GOD.

SERIES RULES:  Each racer will be issued ONE bib number for the entire series.   You must use the same bib number at all races in the series.  Replacement bib numbers will be $10.  The best 6 finishes will count towards the overall series’ standings.

RESULTS:  All results will be submitted to USA Cycling within 48 hours after the official results are final.
directions: PARKING: Parking will be located at the SW entrance of the park. Follow signs to the beach area. For directions please visit http://www.lakehopestatepark.com/directions.html

title: Ohio State Championship | Chestnut Ridge | Ohio Po
Hyde Park Blast Criterium
description: The Hyde Park Blast cycling race shares what is now known as the Ohio Crit Weekend with Columbus\' Tour de Grandview (Friday) and The Madeira Centennial Criterium (Sunday).  Saturday\'s Blast event has become the largest one day competitive road cycling event in Ohio, Kentucky and Indiana, with 500 cyclists registered from more than 22 states with competitors from Canada and South America.
course: An L-shaped course featuring one 180 sweeping turn, two long straightaways, an short, gradual uphill on a narrow road, and a fast downhill.
registration: Online registration closes June 27 at 11:45 p.m. Registration will be available in person at the race on Saturday, June 30 for an additional $10 at registration, which is located at Monteith and Erie Avenue.  Registration and participant parking will be held at the intersection of Erie and Paxton Ave.  Registration opens at 3:30 p.m.
notes: Reserved team parking available: 1 car for every 3 riders pre-reg\'d from the same team.  Reserved parking list will be emailed out after close of pre-registration.
directions: Google address: 3500 Paxton Avenue, Cincinnati, OH 45208.  Reserved team parking is west on Erie Ave - see parking attendants.  All other parking east on Erie Ave.

title: Madeira Centennial Criterium
description: The Madeira Race Committee is pleased to announce continuation of the first-ever bike race held in the heart of Madeira:  The 4th Annual Madeira Criterium, Sunday, June 30th 2013. All categories of criterium racers will be competing from 9:00am – 7:30pm.  Complete with music, food, beer tent, and kids events.  Cyclists will battle for over $7800 in cash and merchandise.  Fun for all!
course: COURSE: Following the same route as last year, the 1 mile course dives in and out of the local streets that make up the central Madeira business district.  Start heading north on Miami, 180 back down to south on Miami, left onto Laurel, right onto Center, right onto Laurel, left onto Miami, turnaround then finish heading north on Miami.   Two wide 180 degree  turns are featured at either end of the 1 mile circuit.  Finish line across from Stockyard Bank this year.
registration: REGISTRATION: Pre-registration is encouraged and can be completed here on BikeReg, or at BioWheels bike shop in Madeira.  Registration on race day is available for an additional $10.  Race day registration closes 30 minutes prior to posted start times.  Staging for events will be done by order of registration.
notes: RULES AND REGULATIONS:  All USA Cycling rules and regulations must be followed and will be enforced.  All riders must have a current USA Cycling racing license or a one-day license.  One-day licenses will be available at check in and can only be used by Cat 5 Men and Cat 4 Women.
directions:
DIRECTIONS:  From Columbus I-71 South, take the Montgomery Rd exit 12.  Turn left on Montgomery Rd.  Turn right on Hosbrook.  At dead end, turn left on Euclid.  Parking will be off of Euclid as you reach Madeira, look for parking signage.

From downtown Cincinnati to I-71 North, take the Kenwood Rd exit 11.  Right turn on Kenwood.  First left turn on Euclid.  Parking will be off of Euclid as you reach Madeira, look for parking signage.
